Author:
Joren Six Defines a correlation measure for histograms. See On measuring the distance between histograms: Sung-Hyuk Chaa, Sargur N. Sriharib (2002) CorrelationMeasure is a bit of a strange name: also distance measures are defined. Side note: java enums are nice.

INTERSECTION

public static final CorrelationMeasure INTERSECTION
The intersection computes the matching areas under the curve. It is a symmetric correlation measure: 1.0 is perfect correlation, 0.0 means no correlation. Symmetric: f(a,b) = f(b,a)
